SIMPLE: enseam
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enseam
<hw>En*seam"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>seam</ets> suture. Cf. <er>Inseam</er>.]</ety>
<def>To sew up; to inclose by a seam; hence, to include; to
contain.</def> <rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enseam</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enseam
<hw>En*seam"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>en-</ets> +
<ets>seam</ets> grease.]</ety> <def>To cover with grease; to defile; to
pollute.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the rank sweat of an <qex>enseamed</qex> bed.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ensear</ent>⟦br⟧
